The gradient/patternTransform properties follow the rules of the CSS

transforms spec:



"If a transform function causes the current transformation matrix of an

displayed." [1]



Check if the relevant transform is non-invertible and flag the paintserver

as invalid if it is.

entry.title: [omnibox] Reports # of zero-prefix suggestions in Autocomplete session.
entry.content:
Omnibox currently reports the number of zero-prefix suggestions shown in

searchboxstats (gs_lcrp=) only if the user selects a zero-prefix

suggestion. In other words, omnibox does not take into account the

zero-prefix suggestions previously shown to the user if they end up

typing and selecting a prefixed suggestion. This is incorrect and makes

a number of otherwise insightful Bsb metrics useless. See

go/chrome-zps-metrics-101 for details on the affected metrics.



This CL introduces the concept of a session in the AutocompleteResult

which is reset when the AutocompleteController resets the

AutocompleteResult - i.e., on popup closing. This is not to be confused

with when the AutocompleteController clears the matches - e.g. on the

last async pass. This allows the session metadata to be carried over

between the "old results" (results from the previous query) to the

"new results" (results from the current query) until the popup is closed. The session metadata is at the moment restricted to the number of zero-prefix suggestions. If it proves to work well, it can also

include the "previous suggestions" in the future.



Pros:

The scope of changes is restricted to the Autocomplete classes allowing

it to work across all platforms (verified by Mobile teams).



Alternative considered:

Building on top of the existing concept of

AutocompleteController::ResetSession() and

OmniboxTriggeredFeatureService. Unfortunately that definition session

does not work for zero-prefix suggestions as it defines a new session

as when the user starts editing the input. Changing that definition

involves making changes to the Omnibox UI classes (not used by Chrome

Android) and to the Mobile platforms codes which takes a much larger

amount of investment.



Future work:

Exploring whether this approach can replace

OmniboxTriggeredFeatureService and whether it can be consolidated with

AutocompleteControllerMetrics for a single more manageable and better

tested metrics. Eventually bringing the concept of session metrics to

OmniboxLog can enable a variety of potentially useful session metrics

to omnibox histograms.

entry.title: Link Query Tiles Instant Fetch to QueryTilesInZPSOnNTP feature.
entry.content:
This change proposes that the QueryTile fetches are not delayed when

the Omnibox feature QueryTilesInZPSOnNTP is enabled.



The retrieval of QueryTiles is delayed by up to 12h, during which we

would not be showing any tiles in the Omnibox. If the user leaves and

kills the application before the fetch is complete, the scheduling is

restarted the next time Chrome is opened.



If Chrome is never kept alive for long enough, the users may never see

QueryTiles.



Omnibox caches internally QT data for (a configurable duration of) 8h.

Once QueryTiles data is retrieved, the Omnibox will not request the

update until that timeout expires (or until Chrome is killed).

entry.title: Remove NavigationURLLoaderImpl::url_chain_
entry.content:
Use `network::ResourceRequest::navigation_redirect_chain` instead,

which records every URL in the redirect chain once.



This is to simplify the logic and make

`NavigationURLLoaderImpl::PrepareForNonInterceptedRequest()`

more like a stateless URLLoaderFactory factory decoupled from

navigation loader's state changes.



Actually these have different values (and are also updated in a

different timings):

- The initial request URL is:

- Always added to `navigation_redirect_chain`

- Not added to `url_chain_` if the first request is intercepted

- Each of subsequent URLs in the redirect chain is:

- Always added once to `navigation_redirect_chain`

- Added twice to `url_chain_` if the redrect leg is not intercepted



However, this doesn't change the behavior in most of the cases,

because only the last two elements of `url_chain_` are used

and the last two elements (at the time of the uses)

are the same before and after this CL,

except for just after the initial request is redirected by a

ServiceWorker.



Thus, the (potential) behavior changes are: After this CL,

- The initiator origin passed to `HandleExternalProtocol` when

the initial request is redirected by ServiceWorker to an

externally-handled URL might be fixed.

- `Navigation.ReceivedResponse` UKMs are no longer collected

for cases involving a redirect by ServiceWorker.



And anyway the new behavior should be correct.

entry.title: [bookmarks] Fix potential ID collisions if one JSON file missing
entry.content:
The scenario should be generally rare, but it is important that

ModelLoader guarantees that node IDs are unique, even when two JSON

files require loading (behind feature flag disabled by default).



If the first JSON file is missing (local-or-syncable nodes), the

behavior before this patch is that permanent nodes use the default node

IDs, namely 1..3. This is problematic when a second JSON file is

involved, because nothing prevents the second JSON file to collide with

those IDs, and no detection mechanism was implemented before this patch.



There are two ways to solve this problem:

A) Those IDs should always be reserved for the local-or-syncable JSON

file and avoided altogether when decoding account nodes.

B) Account nodes are free to use those IDs when the first JSON file

doesn't exist (rare), but then local-or-syncable nodes must be

initialized with non-colliding IDs.



In this patch, option B is chosen because it has one advantange: it

allows to, in the future, rename one JSON file to another without bad

consequences. This is expected to be useful when migrating users that

have sync on, and these bookmarks need to be migrated to be account

bookmarks.

entry.title: [PIX] Change the way we use regex matching
entry.content:
This patch changes the regex matching by adding two groups for the

section id and the section length. This allows not to care about string

to size_t conversion, and gives this responsibility to re2.



This also starts using `re2::RE::Consume` in order to avoid managing

string_view substrings. In other words, as the string is being parsed,

it is also being consumed. An empty string means there is nothing else

to parse. This allows removing `section_end` field in `SectionInfo`,

since this field is not strictly necessary.

entry.title: [Printing] Enrich CupsPrintingNotification for Web Printing API jobs
entry.content:
Jobs initiated by Isolated Web Apps (IWAs) via the Web Printing API do

not require a print dialog which allows these apps to print silently.

To keep the user aware of what is actually happening, it's necessary to

augment the existing printing notification with a few important details:

* The name of the initiating IWA;

* An option to revoke the IWA's permission to print.



To achieve the latter while preserving the existing behavior (open the

print management app on click), the notification is now equipped with

two buttons: one brings the user to the content settings page, and the

other opens the print management app as before.



Note that these changes only apply to jobs submitted via the Web

Printing API; for all others notifications follow the existing model.



On top of that, a few messages are updated to align with the modern

UX guidance:

* Printing started -> Printing...

* Printing complete -> Done



See go/advanced-printer-features-wd for details on wordsmithing.

entry.title: Fix external app cross window navigation
entry.content:
This CL fixes the way external app are opened using

another window



1. disallow cross origin/cross window request.

Cross origin cross window request would lead to the app

opening prompt being displayed on tab A while the request

really comes from tab B, which can lead to user confusion.

Disallow it. There is a chance that this may break some

legitimate flows, so add a kill switch in case this must

be temporarily disabled



2. fix the "transient tab" logic.

There is a logic in which a tab can be used to open an

external application, and then is immediately closed.

The current logic close the target tab and reattributes

the popup to the initiating tab.

This is not working as the closed tab also dealloced

the tabhelper, and so the popup has no handler anymore.

Fix this logic by delaying the tab closing until after

the popup is resolved.

entry.title: Fix passing component policy from Ash to Lacros
entry.content:
Component policy (i.e. policy for extensions) should be passed to

Lacros at first launch. This is currently not happening because at the

time of initializing launch parameters for Lacros, component policy is

not set in EnvironmentProvider yet. This is because BrowserManager

starts observing ComponentPolicyService then continues on to

initializing Lacros launch parameters, while the notification from

ComponentPolicyService happens asynchronously.

This CL fixes this issue by caching the component policy in

ComponentPolicyService and fetching it synchronously when preparing

policies for Lacros, in addition to observing changes in the policy.

entry.title: Rename //net/base/mac directory to //net/base/apple (5/5)
entry.content:
This renames the remaining directory in //net/base used both by macOS

and iOS, following the naming convention and changing it something more

suggestive.



Like suggested by mark@, this renaming process will be carried on in

three steps:



1. Rename net/base/mac to net/base/apple, creating new temporary

forwarding headers in net/base/mac that #include net/base/apple.



2. Convert all of the use sites from net/base/mac to net/base/apple.

This can be done across multiple ch anges if desirable, which could make

things more manageable for reviewers.



3. Remove the temporary forwarding headers in net/base/mac, so that

we’re only left with net/base/apple. The changes here are performing

this step, which is the final of this series.
